Issues.Body:
If use class **System.Windows.Forms.Integration.ElementHost** in Winforms, and then maximize the interface, it will cause a large area of black on the interface background.

https://docs.microsoft.com/en-us/dotnet/api/system.windows.forms.integration.elementhost

Test Code:
.net 6.0

```
using System.Windows.Forms.Integration;

namespace FormBorderTest
{
    internal static class Program
    {
        [STAThread]
        static void Main()
        {
            ApplicationConfiguration.Initialize();

            var form = new Form()
            {
                Width = 600,
                Height = 400,

                StartPosition = FormStartPosition.CenterScreen,
            };

            var host = new ElementHost()
            {
                Dock= DockStyle.Fill,
            };

            form.Controls.Add(host);

            Application.Run(form);
        }
    }
}
```
Test Steps:

Step 1: Double-click the title bar to start maximizing.

![000](https://user-images.githubusercontent.com/88176616/146145942-43043673-8a47-44b6-8dce-04614b0892f1.png)

Step 2: In the process of maximization, a large black area appeared on the entire interface.

![002](https://user-images.githubusercontent.com/88176616/146144681-15da8498-db0b-4766-afbe-5937ad11daf1.png)

Step 3: After being maximized, the interface returns to normal.

![003](https://user-images.githubusercontent.com/88176616/146144689-6cc35132-1d75-47c7-8893-0d6773ee621b.png)
